The scaling factor for calculating own funds, according to the context provided, is:

(a) 0.5 where the payment institution provides only the payment service referred to in point (6) of Annex I;  
(b) 1 where the payment institution provides any of the payment services referred to in any of points (1) to (5) of Annex I.

In the calculation of own funds under PSD2, the multiplication factor is used in Method C and is defined as follows:

- 10% of the slice of the relevant indicator up to EUR 2.5 million;
- 8% of the slice of the relevant indicator from EUR 2.5 million up to EUR 5 million;
- 6% of the slice of the relevant indicator from EUR 5 million up to EUR 25 million;
- 3% of the slice of the relevant indicator from EUR 25 million up to EUR 50 million;
- 1.5% above EUR 50 million.
